author: @bruno5601
text: Actually your detection look a lot more like edge detection (since pixels nearby the edge seems to vary a lot more than the rest of them) and that's why you start jumping in dark places. It's like, you need a little beat of motion to detect edges (the edge will move between pixels so), but actually what your code dos is: If there is not enough edges, jump.  I suppose the most natural way to do it it's detect edges with no motion and act when edges didn't change as much.
